[2
Date: Sat, 17 Jan 1998 15:58:14 -0500
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency (Germany) 17 Jan; OIE Disease Information
(Spain), 16 Jan 1998

Xinhua News Agency has reported today from Bonn that the slaughter of about
77,000 pigs has been ordered by officials in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, North
Rhine-Westphalia, Lower Saxony, and Schleswig-Holstein due to an outbreak
of classical swine fever in one farm and subsequent sale of breeding pigs
to other German states.
Belgium on Friday, 16 January imposed a temporary ban on the sale of pigs
from 90 farms that imported pigs from Germany during the past 40 days.
In Spain, according to a report received on 13 January by the Office
International des Epizooties, there were 2 new outbreaks of the disease in
December, 1997, one in Lerida province, the other in Segovia province. Out
of 17,558 susceptible animals, 98 died and 17,460 were destroyed.
